p:
The differential equations of the SIR model are given as:
 
  (1)
  \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}\begin{eqnarray*} && \frac{\mathrm{d}S(t)}{\mathrm{d}t}=-\beta S(t)\frac{I(t)}{N},\frac{\mathrm{d}I(t)}{\mathrm{d}t}=\beta S(t)\frac{I(t)}{N}-\gamma I(t),\frac{\mathrm{d}R(t)}{\mathrm{d}t} \nonumber\\ && \qquad \,\ = \gamma I(t),S(t)+I(t)+R(t)=N, \end{eqnarray*}\end{document}
  where 
 
  \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}$S(t)$\end{document}
 , 
 
  \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}$I(t)$\end{document}
  and 
 
  \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}$R(t)$\end{document}
  are the number of susceptible, infected and removed people. 
 
  \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}$\beta$\end{document}
  is the infection rate, and 
 
  \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}$\gamma$\end{document}
  is the remove rate which is the inverse of infectious period. The basic reproduction number, 
 
  \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}${R}_0$\end{document}
 , is the average number of the secondary individuals in a complete susceptible population infected by a single infected person during its spreading life. When 
 
  \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}${R}_0>1$\end{document}
 , the virus spreads through the population, and when 
 
  \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}${R}_0<1$\end{document}
  the outbreak will stop due to decreasing the number of new cases. 
 
  \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}${R}_0$\end{document}
  can be calculated as the following:
 
  (2)
  \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}\begin{eqnarray*} && \frac{\mathrm{d}I(t)}{\mathrm{d}t}>0\Rightarrow \beta S(t)\frac{I(t)}{N}-\gamma I(t)>0\Rightarrow I(t)\ \left(\beta \frac{S(t)}{N}-\gamma \right)\nonumber\\ && \,\ \qquad > 0\overset{S(t)\approx N}{\Rightarrow }I(t)\ \left(\beta -\gamma \right) \Rightarrow \beta -\gamma >0\Rightarrow \beta >\gamma \Rightarrow \frac{\beta }{\gamma }\nonumber \\ && \,\ \qquad >1\Rightarrow{R}_0=\frac{\beta }{\gamma } \end{eqnarray*}\end{document}
